TTS Caller (Clojure + MaryTTS + Baresip)

A lightweight voice alert service that converts text to speech (TTS) and initiates SIP phone calls. Built with Clojure, using MaryTTS for speech synthesis and Baresip for SIP call handling.

Perfect for integration with monitoring systems like Zabbix, ElastAlert, Alertmanager, and Centreon.
ðŸš€ How to Run
1. Build the Docker Image

docker build -t tts-caller .

2. Start the Service

docker run --rm -p 8899:8899 --name tts-caller tts-caller

To pass SIP credentials and SIP server host:

docker run --rm -p 8899:8899 \
  -e SIP_USER="0201011221" \
  -e SIP_PASS="yourpassword" \
  -e SIP_HOST="10.22.6.249" \
  --name tts-caller tts-caller

